In building for the future, let us, for once, be clinical and methodical rather than sentimental or emotional. All players over the age of 26 should by the end of this year see off their last matches in the ODI team and should be given notice that none (including Amla, Duminy and Steyn) would be included in the team from next year. It is time to say goodbye to some of these cricketers. You have served your country well. We should all now make way for the future. What the Proteas need is a solid team of young players who can produce a victory by supporting each other on and off the field. There are enough talented young cricketers in South Africa, who need to be mentored and nurtured better. Daily News